  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison sends his condolences to George William Benson on the death of his daughter (Eliza Davis Benson). Garrison also mentions Anna Benson&apos;s illness. Garrison discusses the possible outcome of the debate on the repeal of the Union. Dr. Wesselhoeft is expected to visit Northampton in the morning. Garrison urges George William Benson to attend the New England Anti-Slavery Convention with David Lee Child, William Adam, and Dr. Erasmus Darwin Hudson.</subfield>
